                    </div>
                    <span>Over several years, I have purchased around a dozen books on MFC, and this one by far is not only the best one for learning MFC, but also the best to use as a reference (in addition to MSDN).   Some of the examples were a little lengthy, as I prefer shorter examples.  The first half of the book is essential for any windows programmer.   The second half leans more towards particular advanced topics which are not needed by everyone, but good to have handy when the time comes.</span>
                  
